				\begin{document}$$ y=X\upalpha +P\upbeta +Z\mathrm{u}+\mathrm{e} $$\end{document}y=Xα+Pβ+Zu+ewhere y was phenotype value; α was the vector of SNP effects; β was vector of population structure effects based on PCA; u was vector of kinship background effects; e was vector of residual effects; X, P, Z were incidence matrix relating the individuals to fixed marker effects α, fixed principal component (PC) effects β, random group effects u, respectively.
